<HEADLINE>
EXECUTIVE YUAN TO ANNOUNCE MINIMUM WAGE ADJUSTMENT SOON: VICE
PREMIER
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  May 4 (CNA) 05/04/07  16:58:49 (By Ruth Wang)
</P>
<P>
The Executive Yuan will soon announce an increase in the minimum
wage after having fully consulted with business and industry, and
deciding upon supplementary measures, Vice Premier Tsai Ing-wen
said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Tsai emphasized that the minimum wage adjustment is carved in
stone and certainly will be implemented in July.
</P>
<P>
In order to better protect laborers' rights, the Executive Yuan
is also working on amendments to the Labor Union Law, Collective
Agreement Law, Employment Insurance Act, and Gender Equality in
Employment Law, Tsai said.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the national Federation of Labor Chen Chie said that
laborers are eagerly awaiting an increase of the minimum wage,
which has not been adjusted for more than 10 years.
</P>
<P>
Chen  said  the government  should  pay attention  to the
implementation of the basic wage adjustment, for many laborers
presently do not receive their mandated minimum wage.
</P>
